Data Preparation¶

In [26]:
scaler = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(0, 1))
scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(data['Close'].values.reshape(-1, 1))
prediction_days = 100

x_train, y_train = [], []
for x in range(prediction_days, len(scaled_data)):
    x_train.append(scaled_data[x - prediction_days:x, 0])
    y_train.append(scaled_data[x, 0])

x_train, y_train = np.array(x_train), np.array(y_train)
x_train = np.reshape(x_train, (x_train.shape[0], x_train.shape[1], 1))

split_index = len(x_train) - 300
x_val, y_val = x_train[split_index:], y_train[split_index:]
x_train, y_train = x_train[:split_index], y_train[:split_index]

# Data shapes
print("x_train shape:", x_train.shape)
print("y_train shape:", y_train.shape)
print("x_val shape:", x_val.shape)
print("y_val shape:", y_val.shape)

In [27]:
model1 = Sequential()
model1.add(LSTM(units=100, return_sequences=True, input_shape=(x_train.shape[1], 1)))
model1.add(LayerNormalization())
model1.add(Dropout(0.2))
model1.add(LSTM(units=100, return_sequences=True))
model1.add(LayerNormalization())
model1.add(Dropout(0.2))
model1.add(GRU(units=100, return_sequences=False))
model1.add(LayerNormalization())
model1.add(Dropout(0.5))
model1.add(Dense(units=1))

model2 = Sequential()

Model training¶

In [32]:
# Function for plotting model training metrics vs metrics on validation set
def plot_history(history):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(3, figsize=(8, 12))
    
    # Subplot for loss
    axs[0].plot(history.history['loss'], label='Train Loss')
    axs[0].plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='Validation Loss')
    axs[0].set_title('Loss')
    axs[0].set_xlabel('Epochs')
    axs[0].set_ylabel('Loss')
    axs[0].legend()
    
    # Subplot for mean absolute error
    axs[1].plot(history.history['mean_absolute_error'], label='Train MAE')
    axs[1].plot(history.history['val_mean_absolute_error'], label='Validation MAE')
    axs[1].set_title('Mean Absolute Error')
    axs[1].set_xlabel('Epochs')
    axs[1].set_ylabel('MAE')
    axs[1].legend()
    
    # Subplot for mean absolute percentage error
    axs[2].plot(history.history['mape'], label='Train MAPE')
    axs[2].plot(history.history['val_mape'], label='Validation MAPE')
    axs[2].set_title('Mean Absolute Percentage Error')
    axs[2].set_xlabel('Epochs')
    axs[2].set_ylabel('MAPE')
    axs[2].legend()
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
